content.description: Halfway down the Eddie Corridor, on the right side, if you're walking toward Eddie.  Sit starts on the left side of a shallow cave on a blunt tufa arete.  Traverse the lip and gain a right facing seam ride hand, then go up to a jug and drop off.  "Smash Alley" is painted on the rock below the problem.  Would be a classic problem if you could top it out.

content.description:
LOCATION: Eddie Area A9 in the SCC topo. 

  Start low on the jugs. Move up to right hand sidepull.  Big left hand move out of overhang to jug. Match the jug, and then use a left heel hook to move up to crimp rail.  Big move to the sloper top out; this is the crux. 

  All the holds are chalked up. Downclimb the backside after topping out.
Large curtain of easy slab just right of monorail. Middle is the least easy.
content.location: Corrider behind Oatmeal Boulders

content.description: Start on large right facing flake on face. Move up and right to arete on crimps and pockets. Slap the arete and top out by monorail-ing up the slopey arete.
content.location: Go down corrider behind oatmeal boulders. This climb starts on the left at the far end.

 "Sit start on small undercling slotted crimps, move through a couple crimps. Adjust feet and rocket out to low percentage slotted crimp, thats the first part of the crux. Come in for a match, slap a horrible intermediate and come out to "jug". Finish out the climb with one more powerful move and a desperate throw to the top."

content.description: Sit start at base of steep handcrack. Climb crack with good jams. Either jump off when cracks goes vertical, or keep cruisin up 5.7 crack to the top, exiting to the right into the chimney. Take care with some potentially loose holds up top.Would be easily a 4 star crack boulder if it were not so darn pebbly. Tape accordingly, especially if topping out.If anyone knows the true name of this crack, let me know and Ill update it
content.protection: Could place  a bunch of #2s if you wanted, but no anchor or good gear up on top. Better to boulder
content.location: This is the obvious hand crack on the right side of the corridor when heading towards Eddies/Mystified. Right by a big hueco cave.
